[17.069241, "o", "# Threat Intel Brief — FinSector Credential Harvesting Campaign Q1 2026\r\n\r\n**Source bundle:** `bundle--01-phishing-campaign-2026q1`  \r\n**STIX version:** 2.1  \r\n**Objects in bundle:** 13\r\n\r\n## Executive summary\r\n\r\nThe bundle describes FinSector Credential Harvesting Campaign Q1 2026 [campaign--apt-finsector-2026q1]. Spear-phishing campaign targeting US financial-sector organizations between Feb and April 2026. Phishing emails impersonate internal IT and contain a link to a credential-harvesting page that mimics the target's SSO portal. Captured credentials are exfiltrated to attacker-controlled infrastructure.\r\n\r\n"]
[17.070452, "o", "The campaign is attributed to Mimicry Collective [threat-actor--mimicry-collective] — Financially-motivated threat group active since late 2025. Specializes in credential-harvesting via near-identical clones of corporate SSO portals. Operating tempo is consistent with a small (3-5 person) crew.\r\n\r\n## Indicators of compromise\r\n\r\n- **Phishing domain mimicking ACME SSO** [indicator--phish-domain-acme-sso] — [domain-name:value = 'acme-sso.example-attacker.com']\r\n- **Credential exfiltration C2 endpoint** [indicator--c2-exfil-endpoint] — [url:value = 'https://exfil.example-attacker.com/c2/submit']\r\n- **Phishing landing page (HTML) SHA256** [indicator--phish-page-sha256] — [file:hashes.'SHA-256' = 'a1b2c3d4e5f60718293a4b5c6d7e8f9012345678abcdef0123456789abcdef01']\r\n\r\n## TTPs (MITRE ATT&CK)\r\n\r\n- **Spearphishing via Link (T1566.002)** [attack-pattern--phishing-spearphishing-link] — T1566.002\r\n\r\n## Recommended actions\r\n\r\n- Block listed indicators at the perimeter: [indicator--phish-domain-acme-sso], [indicato"]
[17.070743, "o", "r--c2-exfil-endpoint], [indicator--phish-page-sha256]\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n*Generated by the offline stub client. Every citation in this brief is bound to a real object ID in the source bundle — the citation verifier should report zero hallucinations.*\r\n\r\n"]
